Description:
Requirements:
Master degree or above majoring Electronic Engineering, Automation and Computer Science, PHD。 Is preferred;
4+ professional years in embedded or mobile system R&D with experience on hardware, firmware development and system verification;
Able to apply CAD tools, Oscilloscopes, Signal Generators, A/D Acquisition Instruments, Bus Analyzers;
Able to apply C/C++, Python, Visual Basic, Shell Scripts, etc for some basic development and testing;
Familiar with embedded product development process, industrialization process and experience on yield improvement.
Handy person with preciseness, systematic and logical thinking.
Good English communication skills. Chinese would be definitely a plus.
Some basic knowledge on Optics, Fluidics, Mechanics, or Chemistry/Biology would be definitely a plus.
Job Functions and Qualifications:
Hardware and software architectural design for embedded systems based on micro-controllers or mobile CPUs;
Schematics design, review and modification as well as PCB layout, BOM optimization and management;
Testing, debug and system verification on electrical interfaces as well as software;
Evaluation on development kits for new sensor modules;
Technical documentation, version control of design files;
Cooperation with team members including other engineers and bio-experts for system optimization, quality improvement and cost down;
Technical support for other team members when necessary.
